                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6322.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-23T15:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1913—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>28. The Government has decided to do military honors to the remains of Francisco
                    Madero and José María Pino Suárez and to deliver their remains to their
                    families. The Government has liberated all Deputies who were imprisoned.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
